      • implement

        public void implement​(Class<?> token,
                      Path root)
               throws ImplerException
        Description copied from interface: Impler
        Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

        Generated class' name should be the same as the class name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code should be placed in the correct subdirectory of the specified root directory and have correct file name. For example, the implementation of the interface List should go to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java

        Specified by:
        implement in interface Impler
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for.
        root - root directory.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - if given arguments are incorrect @see checkArgs(java.lang.Class<?>, java.nio.file.Path), or if getHeader(java.lang.Class<?>), getClassBody(java.lang.Class<?>, java.io.BufferedWriter) thrown ImplerException, or if IOException occur during writing implemented class

        public void implementJar​(Class<?> token,
                         Path jarFile)
                  throws ImplerException
        Description copied from interface: JarImpler
        Produces .jar file implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

        implementJar in interface JarImpler
        Parameters:

      • getClassBody

        private void getClassBody​(Class<?> token,
                          BufferedWriter writer)
                   throws ImplerException
        Writes class body

        Writes implementing for all declared abstract not final methods @see implementAbstractMethods(java.lang.Class<?>, java.io.BufferedWriter). If given class isn't an interface writes all declared not private constructors @see implementConstructors(java.lang.Class<?>, java.io.BufferedWriter)

        Parameters:
        token - Class that body will be implemented
        writer - BufferedWriter that writes implementing parts to class file
        Throws:
        ImplerException - if ImplerException thrown in @see implementAbstractMethods(java.lang.Class<?>, java.io.BufferedWriter) or in @see implementConstructors(java.lang.Class<?>, java.io.BufferedWriter)

      • implementAbstractMethods

        private void implementAbstractMethods​(Class<?> token,
                                      BufferedWriter writer)
                               throws ImplerException
        Writes implementing for all declared abstract not final methods

        If class has no such methods then will be written nothing. If method is abstract and final it won't be written

        Parameters:
        token - Class that abstract methods will be implemented
        writer - BufferedWriter that writes implementing methods to class file
        Throws:
        ImplerException - if ImplerException thrown during getting methods in @see getAbstractMethods(java.lang.Class<?>) or in buildUnit(E) or if IOException occur during writing methods
